P. H. Glatfelter Company Key Developments

Glatfelter Appoints Tina M. Moylan as Director, Specialty Inkjet Products
Jun 13 17
Glatfelter announced that Tina M. Moylan joined its Specialty Papers business unit as Director, Specialty Inkjet Products, reporting to David Dickerhoof, Vice President, Sales & Marketing, effective June 12. In this new role, Tina will bring significant industry experience and will be responsible for leading the development of Glatfelter's product portfolio, sales channels and growth strategies for inkjet printable substrates. Tina brings 35 years of experience in the paper industry, including 20 years at Glatfelter in a variety of technical and product development roles. Most recently, Tina's career focused on sales and marketing of inkjet substrates.


P. H. Glatfelter Company Presents at Houlihan Lokey 2017 Global Industrials Conference, May-18-2017 01:45 PM
May 16 17
P. H. Glatfelter Company Presents at Houlihan Lokey 2017 Global Industrials Conference, May-18-2017 01:45 PM. Venue: Hilton Midtown New York, 1335 6th Avenue, New York NY, 10019, United States. Speakers: John P. Jacunski, Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President.


Glatfelter Declares Cash Dividend, Payable on August 1, 2017
May 4 17
Glatfelter announced that its board of directors declared a $0.13 per share cash dividend on its outstanding common stock. The dividend is payable on August 1, 2017, to shareholders of record as of the close of business on July 3, 2017.


