Home > Careers              

	                    









Create Your Own Success Story at Glatfelter
Since 1864, our employees—Glatfelter 
	PEOPLE—have defined our success, working together to create innovative, 
	quality products for millions of people the world over. As an Equal 
	Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employer, Glatfelter employs over 4,300 
	people worldwide in a variety of professional fields including paper 
	manufacturing, mechanical engineering, sales & marketing, customer service, 
	information technology, finance, and administration.

    At Glatfelter, you’ll be part of a strong and growing multi-national 
	company, continuing our success story, as well as your own. Glatfelter 
	employees are people who are passionate about finding innovative solutions 
	for our customers, believe in doing whatever it takes to get the job done, 
	never settle for less than the best, and consistently strive to exceed 
	expectations. In turn, we offer a 
	rewarding, 
	sustainable work environment based on a 
	culture of values. Glatfelter needs people like you. And we’re pleased 
	that you are interested in a career with us.  
    



			What do Glatfelter PEOPLE say about working here?













Get an inside look at the Glatfelter 
							career experience from our employees—Glatfelter 
							PEOPLE—who are living it today.




			What’s kept us successful since 1864?













There’s a reason why we’ve remained a 
							leader for over a century-and-a-half: Shared common 
							values that benefit employees and customers 
							alike—values lived every day by people like you.




			How does Glatfelter offer a sustainable work situation?













Glatfelter views sustainability as more 
							than an environmental initiative. It’s a way of 
							life, shared by Glatfelter PEOPLE and lived every 
							day in the workplace.




			What makes Glatfelter’s global total rewards package so attractive?













Glatfelter puts PEOPLE first by 
							designing total rewards packages to attract, retain, 
							motivate and reward the employees who are crucial to 
							the success of our business.


 
Did You Know?


Glatfelter’s 12 locations include facilities in the U.S., Canada, 
		Europe and Asia, with over 4,300 employees worldwide — with more than 
		800 employees in Pennsylvania alone.
During the Great Depression, despite unemployment as high as 25% at 
		times, Glatfelter never laid off a single employee.
Glatfelter was one of the industry’s pioneers in employee 
		communications, employee safety programs and wellness initiatives.
Glatfelter developed the first sustainably managed tree farms in 
		Pennsylvania and Maryland.
In the early 1960s, Glatfelter partnered with the Commonwealth of 
		Pennsylvania to build Lake Marburg and help create Codorus State Park as 
		an outdoor recreation area for all to enjoy.
Glatfelter began as a single paper mill in Spring Grove, PA, valued 
		at $14,000, and today is a $1.6 billion dollar, global industry leader.
	





